{
  "stem": "23278.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, the poor man was a poet, a violinist who only thought of his art and his music and did that underwear business because it was his parents' business, and he had to make a living.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, he was-- he was nothing suspicious.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But you see, that was the climate.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So what he did, he enlisted into the French army when the war broke.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He did.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He didn't have to, but he did.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because he felt he was going to secure his position and with the children.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Then we had the war.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1939.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And all that happened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then, I mean, not the war, we had what you call the exodus.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The German broke in.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Everybody fled including us, because we were bombed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And on the roads, on the street, we saw Vietnamese, the little Vietnamese.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know, they are small people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We had taken them from our colonies and put them in the ammunition factories and all that.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we abandoned them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there were thumbing their ways.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They looked like children to me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I said to my dad, stop, stop.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But the car was overloaded with everything we had.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And you know, I left my heart with them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So when the Vietnamese war came, you imagine on what side I was.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I mean, that's something I still--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were heading for the south, for my uncle who was living well in the [NON-ENGLISH], where the old protestants used to live near the [NON-ENGLISH], and all that where my uncle's family lives even to this day.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So when we came near Lyon, the Italians machine gunned us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the car went tumbling.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my parents were fine, my sister too.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I was was sitting in the back with a huge jerrycan of gasoline.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
